about.summary: The Rmisc library contains many functions useful for data analysis and utility operations.

name: r-rmisc
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '1.5' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-rmisc
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Rmisc_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/Rmisc/Rmisc_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: c817ff391136735a267183f133b6a262b1d90a9b399fd3e2d52ea43dbc8352c6

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-lattice
    - r-plyr
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-lattice
    - r-plyr

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('Rmisc')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('Rmisc')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=Rmisc
  license: GPL-3
  summary: The Rmisc library contains many functions useful for data analysis and utility operations.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
